<style>
tbody {
    page-break-inside: avoid;
    page-break-before: avoid;
    page-break-after: avoid;
}
tbody::after {
  content: '';
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: 1.5em;
  page-break-before: auto;
  page-break-after: auto;
}
</style>

<div class="mx-auto w-full print:w-full">
  <% if notice.present? %>
    <p class="py-2 px-3 bg-green-50 mb-5 text-green-500 font-medium rounded-lg inline-block" id="notice"><%= notice %></p>
  <% end %>

<div data-controller="info-box">
<div class="info-button">&#x24D8;</div>
<ul class="info-box">
<li>After any changes to a category or heats, you can click the <span class="x-2 rounded-lg py-1 px-2 text-white bg-blue-600 font-medium">Redo</span> button to regenerate the agenda.
<li>Categories affect where each dance appears in the agenda, and are defined on the <%= link_to 'Agenda', categories_path, class: 'x-2 rounded-lg py-1 px-2 text-white bg-blue-600 font-medium' %> page.
<li>The order of Solos within a category is determined by the order in which the Solos appear on the
<%= link_to "Solos", solos_path, class: "x-2 rounded-lg py-1 px-2 text-white bg-green-600 font-medium" %> page.
<li>The <%= link_to "Settings", settings_event_index_path(tab: 'Heats') , class: "x-2 rounded-lg py-1 px-2 text-white bg-blue-600 font-medium" %> page contains some options that allow you to control heat sizes.
<li>If you set the time between start of heats in the settings and add a start time to at least one agenda item,
a scheduled heat time will be added to each heat.
<% if @stats %>
<li>A summary of how many couples are on the floor for each heat is at the <a href="#stats">bottom</a> of this page.
<li>Once the event has "gone to print", clicking the lock icon will lock the agenda preventing large scale changes such as redo. Small changes such as scratching heats, replacing a person in a heat, and even moving an individual entry to another heat is still possible, even when the agenda is locked.
<li>Locking the agenda also captures the heat numbers; if you unlock the agenda and make changes you will see an <span class="x-2 rounded-lg py-1 px-2 text-white bg-blue-400 font-medium">undo</span> button appear that will alow you to revert to the last locked state.
<% end %>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="flex justify-between items-center">
<div class="float-left">
<%= link_to toggle_lock_categories_path(return_to: heats_path), data: { turbo_method: "post" } do %>
<%= image_tag @locked ? 'Padlock-bronze-closed.svg' : 'Padlock-bronze-open.svg', height: 60, width: 60 %>
<% end %>
</div>
  <h1 class="text-center font-bold text-4xl">Agenda</h1>
  <div>
  <%= link_to 'Solos', solos_path, class: "btn-green print:hidden" %>
  <%= up_link 'Redo', redo_heats_path, class: "btn-blue print:hidden", method: :post, disabled: @locked %>
  <%= render partial: 'renumber' %>
  </div>
</div>

  <table class="table-fixed ml-6 mb-8">
    <tr>
      <th class="row-head">Category
      <th colspan="2" class="row-head">Heats
      <% if @start && !@start.compact.empty? %>
      <% unless @oneday %>
      <th class="row-head">Day
      <% end %>
      <th class="row-head" colspan="2">Time
      <% elsif not @oneday %>
      <th class="row-head">Day
      <% end %>
    </tr>
    <% @agenda.each do |cat, heats| %>
      <tr>
        <% if %w(Uncategorized Unscheduled).include? cat %>
        <td class="row text-red-600 font-bold"><a href="#cat-<%= cat.downcase.gsub(/[^\w]+/, '-') %>"><%= cat %></a>
        <% else %>
        <td class="row"><a href="#cat-<%= cat.downcase.gsub(/[^\w]+/, '-') %>"><%= cat %></a>
        <% end %>
        <% if cat == "Unscheduled" %>
        <td colspan="2" class="text-right">(<%= pluralize(Heat.where(number: 0).count, 'entry') %>)
        <% else %>
        <td class="row text-right"><a href="#heat-<%= heats.first&.first %>"><%= heats.first&.first %></a>
        <td class="row text-right"><a href="#heat-<%= heats.last&.first %>"><%= heats.last&.first %></a>
        <% end %>
        <% if @start and @cat_start[cat] %>
        <% unless @oneday %>
        <td class="row"><%= cat == 'Unscheduled' ? '' : Date::DAYNAMES[@cat_start[cat]&.wday || 7] %>
        <% end %>
        <td class="row"><%= cat == 'Unscheduled' ? '' : @cat_start[cat]&.strftime("%I:%M %P") %>
        <td class="row"><%= cat == 'Unscheduled' ? '' : @cat_finish[cat]&.strftime("%I:%M %P") %>
        <% elsif not @categories[cat]&.day.blank? and not @oneday %>
        <td class="row"><%= @categories[cat].day %>
        <% end %>
      </tr>
    <% end %>
  </table>

<% unless @issues.empty? %>
<div class="ml-6 mb-8">
<h2 class="text-red-600 font-bold text-2xl">Issues:</h1>
<ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4">
<% @issues.sort.each do |heat, issues| %>
<% issues.each do |person_id, count| %>
<li>
  <a href="#heat-<%= heat %>">Heat <%= heat %></a>:
  <%= link_to Person.find(person_id).display_name, person_path(person_id) %>
  <% if count == 0 %>
  is not available
  <% else %>
  is on the floor
  <%= count == 2 ? "twice" : "#{count} times" %>
  <% end %>
</li>
<% end %>
<% end %>
</ul>
</div>
<% end%>

  <% @agenda.each do |cat, heats| %>
  <% next if heats.empty? %>
  <div style="page-break-after: always"></div>
  <%= render partial: 'category', locals: {cat: cat, heats: heats} %>
  <% end %>

  <% if @stats %>
  <div>
  <h1 id="stats" class="mt-12 mx-auto font-bold text-4xl print:hidden">Summary</h1>
  <div class="min-w-full print:hidden">
    <table class="mt-4 table-fixed mx-auto">
      <thead>
        <th class="row-head">Couples
        <th class="row-head">Heats
      </thead>

      <% @stats.each do |size, heats| %>
      <% next if size == 1 and (heats - @solos).empty? %>
      <tr>
        <td class="row text-right pr-4"><%= size %>
        <td>
        <% heats.each do |heat| %>
        <% next if size == 1 and @solos.include? heat %>
        <a href="#heat-<%= heat %>"><%= heat %></a>
        <% end %>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <% end %>

      <% unless @solos.empty? %>
      <tr>
        <td class="text-right row pr-4">Solos
        <td>
        <% @solos.each do |heat| %>
        <% next if heat < 0 %>
        <a href="#heat-<%= heat %>"><%= heat %></a>
        <% end %>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <% end %>
    </table>
  </div>
  </div>
  <% end %>
</div>
